nsions%20of%20the%20box.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAccessibility%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ENot%20every%20cat%20is%20agile%20or%20motivated%20enough%20to%20jump%20up%20into%20a%20litter%20box%2C%20and%20top-entry%20boxes%20can%20be%20especially%20challenging%20for%20some%20cats%20to%20access.%20When%20selecting%20a%20box%2C%20consider%20your%20cat's%20mobility%20needs.%20Kittens%2C%20senior%20cats%2C%20and%20those%20with%20injuries%20or%20mobility%20limitations%20may%20benefit%20from%20a%20box%20with%20an%20entry%20height%20of%20about%203%20inches%20or%20less.%20If%20choosing%20a%20box%20with%20a%20high%20entry%20and%20sides%2C%20look%20for%20one%20made%20of%20a%20material%20that%20you%20can%20safely%20modify%20to%20create%20a%20lower%20entry%20that%20better%20suits%20your%20cat's%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDesign%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EQuagliozzi%20says%20cats%20prefer%20a%20box%20that%20doesn't%20distract%20them%20from%20their%20business%20or%20require%20them%20to%20contort%20their%20body%20into%20unnatural%20positions.%20Look%20for%20boxes%20that%20offer%20easy%20entry%20and%20allow%20a%20cat%20to%20stand%20flat%20on%20all%20four%20paws%20rather%20than%20curved%20or%20angled%20boxes.%20An%20open-topped%20litter%20pan%20is%20the%20most%20universally%20accepted%20by%20cats%20of%20all%20types.%20Some%20cats%20may%20be%20intimidated%20by%20hooded%20or%20covered%20litter%20boxes%2C%20especially%20if%20the%20top%20is%20low%20enough%20that%20the%20cat%20must%20crouch%20to%20do%20their%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEase%20of%20cleaning%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20general%2C%20the%20more%20simple%20the%20design%20of%20a%20box%2C%20the%20easier%20it%20will%20be%20to%20clean.%20Litter%20boxes%20should%20be%20scooped%20at%20least%20once%20a%20day%2C%20though%20more%20frequent%20scooping%20is%20ideal.%20Geller%20says%20healthy%20adult%20cats%20typically%20use%20the%20litter%20box%20two%20to%20five%20times%20a%20day%20for%20both%20peeing%20and%20pooping.%20However%2C%20factors%20like%20age%20and%20health%20can%20influence%20this.%20Senior%20cats%20may%20urinate%20more%20often%20due%20to%20conditions%20like%20kidney%20disease%20while%20kittens%20usually%20urinate%20after%20each%20feeding%20and%20may%20poop%20up%20to%20three%20times%20a%20day.%20If%20having%20a%20cover%20over%20your%20litter%20pan%20makes%20you%20forget%20to%20scoop%20it%20daily%2C%20then%20a%20litter%20box%20without%20a%20hood%20is%20a%20more%20hygienic%20option.%20If%20you%20struggle%20to%20scoop%20your%20litter%20box%20daily%2C%20an%20automatic%20or%20smart%20litter%20box%20may%20be%20the%20best%20option%2C%20though%20even%20self-cleaning%20litter%20boxes%20still%20require%20deep%20cleaning.%20Our%20experts%20say%20you'll%20also%20need%20to%20deep%20clean%20your%20litter%20boxes%20every%20four%20to%20six%20weeks%20using%20water%20and%20unscented%20dish%20soap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaterial%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20included%20metal%20and%20plastic%20options%20in%20this%20guide%20to%20the%20best%20cat%20litter%20boxes.%20Plastic%20litter%20boxes%20have%20a%20lower%20upfront%20cost%2C%20but%20our%20experts%20recommend%20replacing%20them%20every%20six%20months%20or%20at%20the%20first%20sign%20of%20scratch%20marks.%20DeVoss%20says%20that%20no%20matter%20how%20well%20the%20box%20is%20cleaned%2C%20scratch%20marks%20accumulate%20bacteria%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20odors.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20stainless%20steel%20and%20metal%20litter%20boxes%20may%20have%20a%20higher%20initial%20cost%2C%20but%20they%20offer%20a%20longer%20lifespan%20compared%20to%20plastic%20options.%20However%2C%20noise-averse%20people%20and%20cats%20alike%20may%20dislike%20the%20sound%20of%20cat%20claws%20on%20metal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2261bc7d94-d5a8-4a1b-9480-5dd6c287d110%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20we%20tested%5C%22%3EHow%20we%20tested%20the%20best%20cat%20litter%20boxes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20white%20and%20orange%20cat%20is%20stepping%20into%20a%20stainless%20steel%20litter%20box.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a3969ebfebcc4d029ddc6f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWe've%20tested%20litter%20boxes%20in%20various%20households%2C%20including%20our%20top%20stainless%20steel%20pick%20from%20Frisco.%3Cp%3EWill%20Fischer%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20five%20years%2C%20we've%20researched%20popular%20litter%20boxes%20from%20major%20online%20retailers%2C%20selecting%20models%20to%20test%20based%20on%20criteria%20provided%20by%20the%20experts%20we%20consulted.%20Freelance%20reporter%20Shoshi%20Parks%20conducted%20the%20initial%20reporting%20for%20this%20guide%20and%20tested%20litter%20boxes%20with%20her%20two%20cats.%20Since%20then%2C%20freelance%20reporter%20Janelle%20Leeson%20and%20three%20Insider%20Reviews%20editors%20and%20reporters%20have%20tested%20additional%20boxes%20with%20six%20more%20cats.%20Although%20we%20haven't%20tested%20our%20DIY%20pick%2C%20it%20meets%20our%20experts'%20criteria%20and%20comes%20from%20a%20trusted%20brand.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20litter%20box%20we%20tested%20was%20used%20for%20at%20least%20one%20month%20and%20evaluated%20using%20the%20methods%20described%20below.%20Unless%20a%20box%20required%20a%20specific%20type%20of%20litter%20to%20operate%20effectively%2C%20testers%20used%20their%20preferred%20substrates%2C%20including%20some%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-cat-litter%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20cat%20litters%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-natural-cat-litter%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20natural%20cat%20litters%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEase%20of%20entry%20test%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20measured%20the%20sides%20of%20each%20box%20and%20the%20height%20of%20any%20openings%20and%20watched%20to%20see%20whether%20our%20cats%20appeared%20to%20have%20difficulty%20accessing%20the%20boxes.%20We%20also%20observed%20how%20our%20cats%20responded%20to%20each%20box%2C%20noting%20which%20they%20preferred%20to%20use%20more%20frequently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETracking%20test%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFor%20each%20litter%20box%20we%20tested%2C%20we%20collected%20the%20litter%20tracked%20onto%20the%20floor%20over%20three%20days%20and%20then%20compared%20the%20quantity%20of%20litter%20between%20boxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECleaning%20test%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20cleaned%20each%20litter%20box%20twice%20daily%2C%20observing%20how%20easy%20it%20was%20to%20access%20and%20remove%20the%20waste%20and%20how%20much%20litter%20stuck%20to%20the%20bottom%20and%20sides%20of%20the%20pan.%20After%20a%20month%20of%20use%2C%20we%20thoroughly%20cleaned%20each%20box%2C%20disposing%20of%20the%20litter%20and%20wiping%20it%20out%20completely.%20We%20noted%20how%20challenging%20the%20boxes%20were%20to%20clean%20and%20approximately%20how%20long%20it%20took.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESize%20test%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20For%20this%20test%2C%20we%20measured%20the%20length%20of%20each%20of%20our%20cats%20when%20standing%20in%20a%20relaxed%20position%20from%20the%20nose%20to%20the%20base%20of%20the%20tail.%20We%20then%20measured%20the%20length%20of%20each%20of%20the%20litter%20box%20contenders%20and%20compared%20the%20numbers.%20We%20favored%20larger%20litter%20boxes%20over%20smaller%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20interviewed%20seven%20experts%20about%20feline%20litter%20box%20habits%20and%20the%20qualities%20to%20look%20for%20in%20a%20good%20litter%20box.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Liza%20Cahn%20is%20a%20veterinarian%20and%20consultant%20for%20Embrace%20Pet%20Insurance.%20She%20is%20also%20a%20freelance%20veterinary%20writer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMolly%20DeVoss%20is%20a%20certified%20feline%20training%20and%20behavior%20specialist%20(CFTBS)%2C%20certified%20cat%20behavior%20consultant%2C%20and%20Fear%20Free%20certified%20trainer%20who%20specializes%20in%20using%20positive%20reinforcement%20to%20modify%20and%20prevent%20unwanted%20behaviors%20in%20cats.%20She%20is%20the%20founder%20and%20owner%20of%20Cat%20Behavior%20Solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Mark%20Freeman%20is%20a%20specialist%20veterinarian%20who%20is%20board-certified%20in%20canine%2Ffeline%20practice%20through%20the%20American%20Board%20of%20Veterinary%20Practitioners%20and%20assistant%20professor%20of%20community%20practice%20at%20Virginia-Maryland%20College%20of%20Veterinary%20Medicine.%20Freeman's%20academic%20and%20research%20interests%20include%20feline%20and%20canine%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaniel%20%26quot%3BDQ%26quot%3B%20Quagliozzi%20is%20a%20cat%20behavior%20consultant%20and%20owner%20of%20Go%20Cat%20Go!%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20California.%20For%20two%20decades%2C%20Quagliozzi%20has%20worked%20with%20cats%20at%20the%20San%20Francisco%20SPCA%2C%20San%20Francisco%20Animal%20Care%20and%20Control%2C%20and%20through%20his%20private%20practice%2C%20Go%20Cat%20Go!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Jamie%20Richardson%20is%20head%20of%20veterinary%20medicine%20at%20Small%20Door%20Veterinary%20in%20New%20York%20City.%20Richardson%20has%20worked%20with%20animals%20around%20the%20world%2C%20from%20South%20Africa%20to%20Hong%20Kong.%20At%20Small%20Door%20Veterinary%2C%20her%20primary%20interests%20besides%20general%20practice%20include%20preventative%20care%2C%20dentistry%2C%20and%20internal%20medicine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Karen%20Sueda%20is%20a%20board-certified%20veterinary%20behaviorist%20who%20was%20practicing%20at%20VCA%20West%20Los%20Angeles%20Animal%20Hospital%20when%20Parks%20interviewed%20her.%20She%20is%20also%20the%20founder%20of%20Karen%20Sueda%20Veterinary%20Behavior%20Inc.%2C%20where%20she%20uses%20positive%2C%20pet-friendly%20behavior%20modification%20techniques%20to%20help%20pet%20owners%20work%20with%20their%20pets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Wailani%20Sung%20is%20a%20board-certified%20veterinary%20behaviorist%20who%20was%20the%20director%20of%20behavior%20and%20welfare%20programs%20at%20the%20San%20Francisco%20SPCA%20Veterinary%20Hospital%20when%20Parks%20interviewed%20her.%20She%20writes%20on%20animal%20behavior%20for%20Vetstreet%2C%20PetMD%2C%20and%20Healthy%20Pet%20magazine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229a8ceda3-56c8-4b76-92a9-ad97ef82e265%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22FAQs%5C%22%3ECat%20litter%20box%20FAQs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20type%20of%20litter%20box%20do%20vets%20recommend%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20isn't%20a%20single%20best%20litter%20box%20for%20every%20cat.%20Our%20experts%20say%20that%20most%20cats%20prefer%20open-top%20litter%20boxes%20that%20provide%20good%20airflow%2C%20easy%20entry%20and%20exit%2C%20unobstructed%20sightlines%2C%20and%20plenty%20of%20room%20to%20circle%20and%20dig.%20However%2C%20some%20cats%20may%20favor%20enclosed%20litter%20boxes%20that%20offer%20more%20privacy.%20Regardless%20of%20the%20style%2C%20the%20litter%20box%20should%20be%20at%20least%201.5%20times%20the%20length%20of%20your%20cat%20from%20their%20nose%20to%20the%20base%20of%20the%20tail.%20Offering%20multiple%20types%20of%20litter%20boxes%20on%20different%20floors%20of%20your%20home%20and%20in%20various%20rooms%20gives%20your%20cat%20the%20opportunity%20to%20choose%20their%20preferred%20design%20and%20location.%20Ease%20of%20access%20is%20also%20important.%20%26quot%3BMake%20sure%20the%20sides%20aren't%20too%20high%20for%20your%20cat%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smalldoorvet.com%2Fteam%2Fdr-jamie-richardson%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Jamie%20Richardson%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20chief%20medical%20officer%20at%20Small%20Door%20Veterinary%20in%20New%20York%20City.%20Boxes%20with%20tall%20sides%20and%20ones%20that%20are%20fully%20enclosed%20or%20top-entry%20can%20make%20some%20cats%20feel%20trapped%2C%20which%20may%20cause%20them%20to%20avoid%20the%20box%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20cats%20prefer%20open%20or%20hooded%20litter%20boxes%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EOpen-topped%20litter%20pans%20are%20the%20most%20widely%20accepted%20boxes%20by%20all%20types%20of%20cats.%20Some%20cats%20may%20feel%20trapped%20and%20be%20afraid%20to%20enter%20hooded%20or%20covered%20litter%20boxes%2C%20particularly%20if%20the%20interior%20height%20is%20so%20limited%20that%20they%20need%20to%20crouch%20while%20eliminating.%20%26quot%3BIf%20your%20cat%20feels%20vulnerable%20and%20unsafe%20in%20the%20litter%20box%2C%20she%20may%20not%20take%20the%20time%20to%20bury%20her%20waste%20after%20elimination%20because%20she%20wants%20to%20get%20out%20of%20there%20quickly%20and%20prevent%20being%20ambushed%20in%20the%20box%2C%26quot%3B%20Geller%20says.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20this%20may%20lead%20to%20your%20cat%20avoiding%20the%20box%20altogether.%20Additionally%2C%20Bell%20says%20covered%20boxes%20trap%20odors%2C%20intensifying%20the%20smell%20for%20cats%2C%20which%20can%20make%20them%20reluctant%20to%20use%20the%20box.%20Doors%20on%20litter%20box%20entrances%2C%20especially%20opaque%20or%20swinging%20ones%2C%20can%20make%20both%20matters%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20type%20of%20cat%20litter%20do%20vets%20recommend%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fliza-cahn-dvm-47824926a%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Liza%20Cahn%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20veterinarian%20and%20consultant%20for%20Embrace%20Pet%20Insurance%2C%20most%20cats%20do%20best%20with%20litter%20that's%20unscented%2C%20clumping%2C%20and%20made%20of%20fine%20grains%2C%20such%20as%20clay%20litter.%20This%20type%20of%20litter%20closely%20resembles%20sand%20or%20dirt%2C%20which%20cats%20might%20choose%20to%20use%20in%20the%20wild.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20a%20litter%20box%20be%20too%20big%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ENo.%20%26quot%3BMost%20cats%20won't%20mind%20a%20box%20that%20is%20a%20bit%20larger%20than%20they%20need%2C%20provided%20you%20keep%20it%20very%20clean%2C%26quot%3B%20Richardson%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20main%20concern%20is%20with%20litter%20boxes%20being%20too%20small.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20many%20litter%20boxes%20do%20I%20need%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESung%20says%20a%20good%20general%20rule%20of%20thumb%20is%20to%20have%20one%20litter%20box%20per%20cat%20plus%20an%20extra.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ksvetbehavior.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Karen%20Sueda%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20board-certified%20veterinary%20behaviorist%2C%20notes%20that%20some%20multi-cat%20households%20can%20get%20by%20with%20fewer%20boxes%20if%20they're%20extra%20large%20and%20scooped%20at%20least%20twice%20a%20day.%20You%20should%20also%20place%20boxes%20in%20different%20areas%20throughout%20your%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhere%20should%20I%20put%20my%20cat's%20litter%20box%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ELitter%20boxes%20should%20be%20placed%20in%20multiple%20locations%20throughout%20your%20home%2C%20including%20on%20each%20level%2C%20and%20kept%20away%20from%20noisy%20appliances%20like%20washers%20or%20dryers%20that%20could%20startle%20your%20cat.%20While%20you'll%20want%20to%20avoid%20busy%2C%20high-traffic%20areas%2C%20the%20box%20should%20still%20be%20close%20to%20where%20your%20cat%20likes%20to%20spend%20time%20with%20you.%20Geller%20says%20that%20a%20cat's%20field%20of%20vision%20also%20matters.%20Rather%20than%20placing%20a%20litter%20box%20tightly%20in%20a%20corner%2C%20setting%20it%20about%2012%20inches%20away%20from%20walls%20can%20improve%20your%20cat's%20view%20of%20their%20surroundings%20and%20help%20them%20feel%20more%20secure.%20Richardson%20also%20notes%20that%20litter%20boxes%20should%20be%20separated%20from%20the%20feeding%20areas.%20%26quot%3BCats%20typically%20don't%20like%20to%20go%20where%20they%20eat%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20often%20should%20I%20clean%20the%20litter%20box%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20keep%20a%20cat%20happily%20using%20their%20litter%20boxes%2C%20our%20experts%20recommend%20scooping%20them%20at%20least%20once%20a%20day%2C%20if%20not%20several%20times.%20In%20addition%20to%20daily%20maintennce%2C%20the%20litter%20box%20should%20be%20cleaned%20with%20unscented%20dish%20soap%20and%20water%20every%20four%20to%20six%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20frequently%20does%20a%20cat%20use%20their%20litter%20box%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20typical%20cat%20uses%20the%20litter%20box%20as%20many%20as%20half%20a%20dozen%20times%20a%20day%2C%20urinating%20two%20to%20four%20times%20and%20defecating%20once%20or%20twice.%20Some%20cats%20may%20go%20more%20or%20less%20frequently%20on%20average.%20Cleaning%20your%20litter%20boxes%20at%20least%20once%20a%20day%20will%20help%20you%20monitor%20for%20medical%20or%20behavioral%20changes%20that%20may%20indicate%20a%20health%20problem%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.avma.org%2Fresources%2Fpet-owners%2Fpetcare%2Ffeline-lower-urinary-tract-disease%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efeline%20lower%20urinary%20tract%20disease%20(FLUTD)%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20is%20my%20cat%20peeing%20outside%20the%20litter%20box%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20your%20cat%20is%20urinating%20or%20defecating%20outside%20of%20the%20litter%20box%2C%20see%20your%20vet%20to%20rule%20out%20medical%20issues%2C%20such%20as%20urinary%20tract%20infection%2C%20cystitis%2C%20or%20arthritis%2C%26quot%3B%20Cahn%20says.%20If%20your%20cat%20gets%20a%20clean%20bill%20of%20health%2C%20she%20recommends%20taking%20a%20closer%20look%20at%20your%20litter%20box%20setup%3A%20Do%20you%20have%20the%20recommended%20number%20of%20boxes%20placed%20in%20different%20areas%20%E2%80%94%20one%20per%20cat%2C%20plus%20one%20extra%3F%20Are%20the%20boxes%20spread%20throughout%20your%20home%20in%20easily%20accessible%20locations%3F%20Do%20you%20scoop%20them%20daily%3F%20Cahn%20also%20recommends%20thoroughly%20cleaning%20any%20soiled%20areas%2C%20offering%20a%20variety%20of%20litter%20types%20(both%20clumping%20and%20non-clumping)%2C%20reducing%20stressors%2C%20increasing%20enrichment%2C%20and%20finally%2C%20consulting%20a%20veterinary%20behaviorist%20if%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-cat-litter-boxes%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1768427382000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6851be3e85e81483682c4582%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-cat-litter-boxes%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20best%20cat%20litter%20boxes%20are%20easy%20to%20clean%20and%20control%20odors.%20Our%20top%20tested%20picks%20are%20extra%20large%2C%20high-sided%2C%20stainless%20steel%2C%20and%20covered%20boxes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Janelle%20Leeson%2CJulie%20Liu%2C%20DVM)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-cat-litter-boxes%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Microsoft%20promised%20consumers%20won't%20foot%20the%20bill%20for%20its%20data%20centers.%20Our%20interactive%20map%20shows%20where%20its%20facilities%20are%20located.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221752%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22trump%20and%20tech%20leaders%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6968033e64858d02d2185eba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221168%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EChip%20Somodevilla%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMicrosoft's%20president%20said%20it%20will%20ensure%20its%20data%20center%20electricity%20costs%20are%20not%20passed%20on%20to%20residential%20customers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20tech%20giant%20filed%20permits%20for%2044%20data%20centers%20nationwide%20as%20of%202024%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Business%20Insider%20tally.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20announcement%20comes%20amid%20backlash%20over%20rising%20electricity%20costs%20and%20President%20Trump's%20%3Ca%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-credit-card-interest-mortgage-rates-mbs-plan-mark-zandi-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaffordability%20push%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20backlash%20intensifies%20against%20data%20centers%20nationwide%2C%20Microsoft%20says%20it%20has%20a%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe'll%20pay%20our%20way%20to%20ensure%20our%20datacenters%20don't%20increase%20your%20electricity%20prices%2C%26quot%3B%20Brad%20Smith%2C%20Microsoft's%20president%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblogs.microsoft.com%2Fon-the-issues%2F2026%2F01%2F13%2Fcommunity-first-ai-infrastructure%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblog%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%20one%20day%20after%20President%20Trump%20said%20in%20a%20Truth%20Social%20post%20that%20he%20does%20not%20want%20Americans%20to%20%26quot%3Bpick%20up%20the%20tab%26quot%3B%20for%20data%20center%20electricity%20costs.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-microsoft-will-ensure-americans-dont-pay-for-data-centers-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%2C%20he%20said%2C%20was%20%26quot%3Bfirst%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20announcement%20comes%20amid%20an%20unprecedented%20data%20center%20construction%20boom%20across%20the%20US.%20Developers%20filed%20permits%20for%201%2C240%20data%20centers%20in%20the%20US%20as%20of%202024%20%E2%80%94%20roughly%20quadruple%20the%20level%20in%202010%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-data-center-development-true-cost-environmental-impact-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%202025%20Business%20Insider%20investigation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20it%20has%20come%20concerns%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felectric-bills-rise-13-states-because-big-tech-data-centers-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erising%20consumer%20electricity%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20grassroots%20opposition%20to%20construction%20buildouts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20filed%20permits%20for%2044%20data%20centers%20as%20of%20the%20end%20of%202024%2C%20Business%20Insider%20found%2C%20the%20fifth%20highest%20count%20in%20our%20analysis.%20Half%20of%20Microsoft's%20permitted%20facilities%20are%20among%20the%20very%20largest%20in%20the%20analysis%20%E2%80%94%20the%20322%20massive%20data%20centers%20that%20we%20estimated%20consume%2040%20megawatts%20of%20electricity%20or%20more%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20a%20look%20at%20where%20Microsoft's%20data%20centers%20are%20found%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FGomiL%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20map%20showing%20location%20of%20known%20data%20centers%2C%20with%20symbols%20sized%20by%20low-end%20estimated%20power%20consumption.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FGomiL%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ETwenty-four%20of%20Microsoft's%20data%20centers%20are%20located%20in%20Virginia%20as%20of%202024%2C%20followed%20by%20Texas%20with%20eight%2C%20and%20Illinois%20and%20Iowa%20each%20with%20four%2C%20according%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20count.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft's%20data%20centers%20are%20extremely%20electricity-intensive%2C%20Business%20Insider's%20analysis%20suggests.%20Its%20most%20power-intensive%20facility%20as%20of%202024%20is%20in%20Maricopa%20County%2C%20Arizona%2C%20according%20to%20the%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon's%20177%20data%20centers%20are%20on%20pace%20to%20command%20the%20highest%20electricity%20demand%20in%20Business%20Insider's%20analysis%20at%20between%2030%20and%2048%20terawatt-hours%20a%20year.%20Microsoft%20%E2%80%94%20with%20only%20around%20a%20quarter%20of%20Amazon's%20facilities%20%E2%80%94%20claims%20the%20next-highest%20spot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FyDueL%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Chart%20showing%20range%20of%20electrical%20power%20used%20by%20data%20centers%20for%20major%20tech%20companies.%20Amazon%20ranks%20first%2C%20with%20power%20use%20between%2030%20and%2048%20terawatt-hours%20per%20year%2C%20followed%20by%20Microsoft%2C%20QTS%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20Meta.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FyDueL%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20reached%20in%202025%2C%20a%20Microsoft%20spokesperson%20acknowledged%20that%20its%20data%20centers%20%26quot%3Bdo%20not%20always%20run%20at%20100%25%20of%20their%20installed%20capacity.%26quot%3B%20Amazon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-calculate-data-center-cost-environmental-impact-methodology-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisputed%3C%2Fa%3E%20Business%20Insider's%20methodology%2C%20and%20QTS%20declined%20to%20comment.%20Google%20and%20Meta%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20all%20of%20Microsoft's%2044%20permitted%20facilities%20come%20online%2C%20their%20electricity%20demand%20could%20reach%20between%2016%20and%2025%20terawatt-hours%20a%20year%2C%20according%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20estimate.%20The%20midpoint%20of%20that%20range%20is%20about%20as%20much%20electricity%20as%201.8%20million%20US%20homes%20based%20on%20average%20annual%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20every%20permitted%20facility%20in%20Business%20Insider's%20dataset%20comes%20online%2C%20their%20electricity%20demand%20could%20reach%20between%20149.6%20terawatt-hours%20and%20239.3%20terawatt-hours%20annually%2C%20Business%20Insider's%20investigation%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20low%20end%20of%20Business%20Insider's%20estimate%20is%20roughly%20equivalent%20to%20the%20state%20of%20Ohio's%20electricity%20needs%20in%202023%2C%20and%20on%20the%20high%20end%2C%20is%20nearly%20as%20much%20power%20as%20the%20entire%20state%20of%20Florida%20used%20that%20same%20year.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fescholarship.org%2Fuc%2Fitem%2F32d6m0d1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2024%20federal%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20projects%20demand%20could%20reach%20levels%20at%20the%20higher%20end%20of%20Business%20Insider's%20estimates%20by%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20location%20of%20data%20centers%20has%20sparked%20a%20surge%20in%20community%20outcry%2C%20with%20neighboring%20residents%20concerned%20about%20their%20impact%20on%20rising%20electricity%20prices.%20Data%20centers'%20extreme%20electricity%20demand%20frequently%20requires%20utilities%20to%20build%20out%20new%20grid%20infrastructure.%20Utilities%20often%20socialize%20the%20investment%20costs%2C%20shifting%20billions%20of%20dollars%20of%20costs%20to%20all%20ratepayers%2C%20including%20residential%20customers%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-centers-tax-subsidies-jobs-ohio-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20Business%20Insider%20investigation%20found%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUtilities%20can%20fund%20discounts%20to%20Big%20Tech%20by%20socializing%20their%20costs%20through%20electricity%20prices%20charged%20to%20the%20public%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feelp.law.harvard.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FHarvard-ELI-Extracting-Profits-from-the-Public.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2025%20Harvard%20Law%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20regulatory%20proceedings%20about%20utility%20rates%20for%20data%20centers%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20ensure%20Microsoft's%20data%20centers%20do%20not%20increase%20residential%20electricity%20bills%2C%20Smith%2C%20Microsoft's%20president%2C%20wrote%20that%20the%20tech%20giant%20plans%20to%20ask%20utilities%20and%20regulators%20to%20set%20the%20company's%20rates%20high%20enough%20to%20cover%20its%20data%20centers'%20electricity%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%20pointed%20to%20Microsoft's%20recent%20support%20of%20new%20electricity%20rates%20that%20charge%20%26quot%3Bvery%20large%20customers%2C%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20data%20centers%2C%20for%20the%20costs%20incurred%20to%20provide%20them%20with%20electricity.%20Smith%20also%20said%20that%20when%20grid%20infrastructure%20improvements%20were%20necessary%20to%20serve%20its%20data%20centers%2C%20the%20company%20would%20pay%20for%20those%20improvements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20the%20long-term%20success%20of%20AI%20infrastructure%20requires%20that%20tech%20companies%20pay%20their%20own%20way%20for%20the%20electricity%20costs%20they%20create%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20promise%20comes%20amid%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-credit-card-interest-mortgage-rates-mbs-plan-mark-zandi-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebroader%20affordability%20push%20from%20President%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20plans%20to%20lower%20mortgage%20rates%20and%20cap%20credit%20card%20interest%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20Hannah%20Beckler%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ahbeckler%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ehbeckler%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20hbeck