r%20on%20the%20idea%2C%20saying%20that%20Trump%20%26quot%3Bprobably%20had%20not%20thought%20through%26quot%3B%20the%20potential%20downsides%20of%20the%20policy%2C%20including%20the%20possibility%20that%20credit%20card%20companies%20would%20%26quot%3Bjust%20stop%20lending%20money%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bcap%20what%20people%20are%20able%20to%20borrow%20at%20a%20very%20low%20amount.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-leaders-respond-trump-plan-cap-credit-card-interest-rate-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBusiness%20leaders%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20offered%20mixed%20reviews%20of%20Trump's%20proposal%2C%20with%20some%20making%20the%20same%20argument%20as%20Johnson.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAn%20interest%20rate%20cap%20is%20not%20something%20that%20we%20would%2C%20or%20could%2C%20support%2C%20frankly%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fciti-cfo-credit-card-cap-would-have-a-deleterious-impact-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECiti's%20chief%20financial%20officer%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20Mark%20Mason%2C%20said%20on%20a%20call%20with%20reporters.%20%26quot%3BAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20I%20think%20an%20interest%20rate%20cap%20would%20restrict%20access%20to%20credit%20to%20those%20who%20need%20it%20the%20most%2C%20and%20frankly%20would%20have%20a%20deleterious%20impact%20on%20the%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbilt-2-credit-card-capped-10-percent-interest-trump-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1768420793000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6967dc0564858d02d21858a4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbilt-2-credit-card-capped-10-percent-interest-trump-2026-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Trump%20recently%20called%20for%20a%2010%25%20cap%20on%20credit%20card%20intere